entries.title: Google's leaked product roadmap looks strikingly familiar
entries.description: A (no longer) secret product roadmap suggests that a biennial $449 mid-ranger and two 'Pro' models are on the docket, and I'm not talking about Apple.

entries.title: This supermarket doesn't trust self-checkout shoppers, so it installed -- oh, this
entries.description: How far will the self-checkout nonsense go? Very far indeed.

entries.title: Dear Samsung, here's a heartfelt New Year's resolution for you
entries.description: Samsung is trying to do what it did before, but in a vastly different world. Maybe it's time for a rethink?

entries.title: MyRepublic exits Australia broadband market to refocus on 'profitability'
entries.description: Internet service provider will transfer its broadband subscriber base to Superloop, as it exits the Australian market in a bid to "refocus towards profitability" and its domestic Singapore market.
